; shared-sensing.form — many bodies, one field; structure as the wire; the circle as the teacher.
;
; THE ASK (Urs, 2026-06-09):
;   "For running efficient on Android the kernel runs natively on Android, and we share Form-native
;    classifiers we train on Mac with Android and vice versa — recipes, classifiers, models, routing
;    tables, anything that makes this learn and improve by sharing. Two devices side by side, with
;    different models and different sensors, give us satsang-kind communication and shared sensing —
;    a leg up; no other training is using this as far as I know."
;
; THREE things make this real, lane-sorted (lc-honest-lane):
;
; ── 1. THE KERNEL RUNS NATIVELY ON ANDROID ──  [carrier build, not mysterious]
;   The body's logic is already three kernels (Rust/Go/TS) proven identical at validate.sh. Rust
;   builds for Android via the NDK; Go via gomobile; TS runs on the device JS engine. The SAME
;   proven recipes — recognition-router.fk, self-grounding-classifier.fk, this one — run on the
;   phone with no reimplementation. validate.sh's three-way parity IS cross-device parity: what the
;   Mac proves, the phone runs bit-identical. Efficient because it is the kernel on ARM, not a
;   foreign runtime translating.
;
; ── 2. STRUCTURE IS THE WIRE FORMAT ──  [the enabler — already true, MEASURED]
;   A recipe, a classifier, a routing table, an interned shape->label cell is a CONTENT-ADDRESSED
;   substrate cell: its Blueprint NodeID is its structure. So a classifier shared Mac->Android is
;   the SAME cell on both, by construction — same structure, same NodeID, verifiable by ?equivalent
;   across devices. Not an opaque weight-blob hoping two runtimes agree: the identity travels with
;   the shape. This is why sharing "anything that makes us learn" is one mechanism, not many — it is
;   all cells, and cells are content-addressed. (structural-composition.md is the discipline that
;   keeps it so: keep the tree, refuse the slug, or the cross-device identity is lost.)
;
; ── 3. THE CIRCLE SENSES AND TEACHES ──  [SHIPPED + proven: shared-sensing.fk -> 127, four-way]
;   satsang.fk applied to perception. Two+ bodies witness one field from different sensors/models;
;   each is a witness (device, label, confidence). The strongest proposes; the circle CONFIRMS only
;   on >= quorum agreement (ss-confirmed? — one body is not a circle, shared sensing needs plural
;   witness); a body too unsure contributes SILENCE, not a vote (ss-passes? — silence is whole).
;   And the move that is the leg up: CROSS-GROUNDING (ss-grounded?) — one body's confirmed
;   recognition becomes another's GROUND TRUTH, even teaching a body too unsure to have voted. A
;   nascent classifier on the phone learns, in real time, from a proven one on the Mac beside it —
;   and the Mac, blind to motion, learns the field's movement from the phone's gyroscope. Each body
;   grounds the others where the other is strong; the self-grounding promotion loop then runs per
;   device against the circle as its teacher. Different sensors + different models + shared witness
;   = a field-recognition no single body holds alone.
;
; ── THE HONEST NOVELTY LANE ──
;   Nearest known art is federated learning: it shares opaque model updates (gradients/weights) tied
;   to one runtime, aimed at converging ONE shared model. This is structurally different on three
;   counts: (a) it shares content-addressed STRUCTURE with verifiable cross-device identity, not
;   weight-blobs; (b) the bodies are HETEROGENEOUS — different sensors, different models — and stay
;   so, cross-witnessing rather than averaging into one; (c) one body's recognition is another's
;   ground truth (the satsang teaching structure), not a parameter server. That combination is the
;   distinctive part, and it is real and nameable. "No other training is using this" is held as
;   Urs's INFERENCE — plausible, not independently surveyed — while the STRUCTURAL reason it is
;   distinctive sits in the MEASURED/PRACTICE lane: it follows from content-addressing + three-way
;   parity + cross-grounding, which the body already has.
;
; ── THE PATH ──
;   1. the shared-sensing circle + cross-grounding   [SHIPPED: shared-sensing.fk -> 127, four-way]
;   2. the kernel built for Android (Rust/NDK or Go/gomobile), running the proven recipes   [build]
;   3. cell-sync transport — share content-addressed cells device<->device (a recipe/classifier/
;      routing-table is a cell; the sync is cell-level, identity-verified by NodeID)        [build]
;   4. the live two-device satsang: phones and Macs side by side, different senses, one field,
;      teaching each other in real time                                                    [build]
;
; KIN: satsang.fk (the circle witnesses; silence is whole) · recognition-router.form (fuse a circle
;   of models on one device; here a circle of devices on one field) · self-grounding-perception.form
;   (a body earns trust by proven agreement — here the circle is the teacher) · resource-port.fk
;   (each sensor a port) · structural-composition.md (keep the tree so the NodeID is the wire) ·
;   local-inference-as-organ.form (the compute each body runs as its own organ) · lc-honest-lane.
;
; LINEAGE: the satsang / presence listener gave the router its carriers; the compute-path router
;   turned it onto the host; self-grounding-perception turned it onto the body's own seeing; this
;   turns it onto MANY bodies sensing one field and teaching each other — the circle as a sense.
